---

## **PROCUREMENT DIRECTOR'S SUMMARY — Q4 CYCLE**

**Cycle Overview:** Full inventory survey across four components; market 
intelligence on flagged items; sourcing evaluation for controller_board_v3 
(target 10k units) and harness_assembly_a (critical single-source gap); 
negotiation strategy on Meridian's non-standard exclusive proposal.

**Components Addressed:**

1. **controller_board_v3** (CRITICAL): On-hand 4,200 units (2.1 weeks cover, 
1,800 units below threshold). 
   - **Primary Award:** Helix Microsystems, 10,000 units @ $39.80/unit = 
**$398,000 USD** (approved supplier, 6-year partnership, 99.4% on-time, zero 
exclusivity lock-in).
   - **Escalation:** Meridian Components proposed 36-month exclusive + $2M 
upfront ($30/unit, 12% lower pricing but unverified reliability). Negotiator 
recommended counter-proposal: 12-month pilot non-exclusive with performance 
gates ($400k upfront, path to full 36-month exclusive only if quality/lead-time 
gates met). **Director decision required:** Accept counter, reject exclusive, or
pursue alternative path.
   - **Status:** Awaiting Helix confirmation and Meridian response to 
counter-terms.

2. **harness_assembly_a** (CRITICAL): On-hand 2,800 units (3 weeks cover, 1,200 
units below threshold).
   - **Primary Award:** Arc Wirecraft, 12,000 units @ $16.20/unit = **$194,400 
USD** (only approved supplier in current registry).
   - **Critical Risk Flagged:** 100% single-source dependency. Arc capacity is 
constrained, on-time performance declining (96% vs. 98% prior quarter), lead 
time 7 weeks. Procurement agent has drafted capacity reservation request to Arc 
(awaiting response).
   - **Contingency:** Urgent third-party supplier discovery RFQ (external 
harness OEMs) authorized pending **human approval**. Parallel qualification 
sprint (2–4 weeks) to identify secondary supplier and mitigate single-source 
risk.
   - **Status:** Arc engagement in flight; third-supplier discovery pending 
director authorization.

3. **lithium_cell_18650** & **thermal_paste_xt**: Both above reorder threshold 
(9.4 weeks and 14 weeks of cover, respectively). No action required this cycle; 
routine reorder cadence maintained.

**Escalations Pending Human Review:**

- **Meridian Exclusive Negotiation** (controller_board_v3): Counter-proposal 
(12-month pilot + gates) vs. reject vs. alternative — **director strategy 
decision required.**
- **harness_assembly_a Single-Source Mitigation** (above): Authorization to 
launch urgent third-party supplier RFQ (~$15k–$25k budget, 90-day qualification 
sprint) — **director approval required.**
- **Mesh HITL** (both awards): Both Helix ($398k) and Arc ($194.4k) purchases 
exceed $50k threshold and require mesh gating.

**Total Q4 Procurement Spend:** **$592,400** (both awards HITL-gated). Substrate
cost inflation (+6%) and labor passthrough (+3%) reflected in pricing; no 
multi-year price locks secured pending Meridian decision.

**Next Steps:** (1) Director review and approval of award recommendation 
document. (2) Director decision on Meridian counter-strategy. (3) Director 
authorization for third-supplier discovery RFQ. (4) Finalize contracts with 
Helix and Arc (always HITL-gated). (5) Monitor Meridian and Arc responses; 
escalate any counter-proposals or contingencies.
